# Mini-Project: Interactive Pet

<div style="background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px; margin-bottom:25px;">

<p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; ">In Lesson 14 of the Creating Apps for Devices unit, students will create an interactive pet using the LED screen and sensors on the micro:bit and physical materials. Students explore how the micro:bit can augment physical materials to create an interactive experience. This project does not use the App Lab screen except to help with debugging - otherwise, users only interact with the physical materials itself.</p></div>

